The Nigerian Female National Cricket Team, the female Yellow-Green will begin their final camping exercise for the forthcoming Nigeria International Women T20 Tournament in Lagos from Monday -March 14, 2022. This follows the trimming down of the 36 invited players for camping at the Edo Boys High School High performance center to 18 after ten days of camping. According a source at the Nigeria Cricket Federation,   Women’s T20 tourney, litmus test for Nigeria, Obalola says     And Tiger wept! Woods breaks down after induction into…     Uysk: Joshua makes Wilder No1 choice in four-man shortlist   The final camping in Lagos , according to NCF, will give opportunities to new talents, especially those that were recommended by selectors from the PwC National Under 17 Championship recently held in Abuja. The players that made the final camping round in Lagos includes captain of the team, Blessin Etim, Sunday Salome, Abigail Igbobie, Agatha Obulor, Asika Omonye, Blessing Frank, Lucky Piety, Queen Joseph, Taiwo Abdulquadir, Peculiar Agboya, Lillian Ude, Favour Eseigbe, Rukayya Abdulrasaq, Rachel Samson, Mary Desmond and Miracle Imimole. The team is expected to be further trimmed to 14 players that would champion Nigeria’s campaign at the coming International T20 Tournament billed for Lagos from March 26 to April 4.